race.comment: Pretty weak race where the second favourite is coming through picnic form. DIAMANDA (4) strung together three wins on end at the picnics then stepped out over much further last time at Cranbourne and held on for a placing. On the quick back-up and well back in journey but carried 77kg to a four length win two back. Should be going close with almost 20kg less here. NIGHT ERUPTION (11) has been beaten four length last two in tougher races so comes right into this. Ran on well for fourth latest and drawn for a good run. AVONVIEW (3) was narrowly beaten last time and is close to a win. Drawn to feature. SPIRIT ANGEL (7) was a Hanging Rock winner two back then solid latest. Among the chances.
